A toddler's mother was overjoyed today after her son was given the all-clear from four tumours despite doctors first suggesting he just had constipation.

Sophie Maloney refused to accept the initial diagnosis on her son Oliver and a local GP said that the lump in his tummy could be to do with his bladder.

An MRI scan revealed he had a large tumour on his prostate, rib, and others on his spine and left thigh.

